<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">Puccinellia laevis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Beal) Ponert
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="113" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="12" pageNumber="113">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="12" pageNumber="113">
There are various variety names included in the autonymic var. 
<taxonomicName class="Monocotyledoneae" family="Gramineae" genus="Puccinellia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="var. secunda" order="Poales" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="variety" species="laevis" variety="secunda">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">secunda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Variety 
<taxonomicName class="Monocotyledoneae" family="Gramineae" genus="Puccinellia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="sandbergii" order="Poales" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="sandbergii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">sandbergii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is 
<taxonomicName class="Monocotyledoneae" family="Gramineae" genus="Puccinellia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="secunda" order="Poales" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="secunda">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">secunda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
s.s.; vars. 
<taxonomicName class="Monocotyledoneae" family="Gramineae" genus="Puccinellia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="elongata" order="Poales" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="elongata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">elongata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Monocotyledoneae" family="Gramineae" genus="Puccinellia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="leckenbyi" order="Poales" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="leckenbyi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">leckenbyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Monocotyledoneae" family="Gramineae" genus="Puccinellia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="laevigata" order="Poales" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="laevigata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">laevigata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Monocotyledoneae" family="Gramineae" genus="Puccinellia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="rigida" order="Poales" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="rigida">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">rigida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
represent the 
<taxonomicName class="Monocotyledoneae" family="Gramineae" genus="Puccinellia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="canbyi" order="Poales" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="canbyi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">canbyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
form; and vars. 
<taxonomicName class="Monocotyledoneae" family="Gramineae" genus="Puccinellia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="incurva" order="Poales" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="incurva">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">incurva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Monocotyledoneae" family="Gramineae" genus="Puccinellia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="saxatilis" order="Poales" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="saxatilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">saxatilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Monocotyledoneae" family="Gramineae" genus="Puccinellia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="buckleyana" order="Poales" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="buckleyana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">buckleyana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Monocotyledoneae" family="Gramineae" genus="Puccinellia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="stenophylla" order="Poales" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="stenophylla">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">stenophylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
represent the 
<taxonomicName class="Monocotyledoneae" family="Gramineae" genus="Puccinellia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="incurva" order="Poales" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="incurva">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">incurva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
form. Varieties 
<taxonomicName class="Monocotyledoneae" family="Gramineae" genus="Puccinellia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="incurva" order="Poales" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="incurva">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">incurva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Monocotyledoneae" family="Gramineae" genus="Puccinellia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="saxatilis" order="Poales" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="saxatilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">saxatilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are generally subalpine to alpine with slightly open panicles; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.65332" author="Hitchcock, AS" journalOrPublisher="Carnegie Institution of Washington publication" pageId="15" pageNumber="116" refId="B17" refString="Hitchcock, AS, 1951. Manual of the Grasses of the United States (2nd edn, A. Chase). US Department of Agriculture, Washington, D.C. https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.65332" title="Manual of the Grasses of the United States (2 nd edn, A. Chase). US Department of Agriculture, Washington, D. C." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.65332" year="1951">Hitchcock (1951)</bibRefCitation>
included them within 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. gracillima" order="Poales" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="gracillima">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">P. gracillima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but 
<bibRefCitation author="Keck, DD" journalOrPublisher="Carnegie Institution of Washington publication" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" refId="B20" refString="Keck, DD, 1959. Poa L. In: PA Munz (Ed.) A California Flora. University of California Press, Berkeley and Los Angeles." title="Poa L. In: PA Munz (Ed.) A California Flora. University of California Press, Berkeley and Los Angeles." year="1959">Keck (1959</bibRefCitation>
and annotations) treated them as 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. incurva" order="Poales" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="incurva">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">P. incurva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Vars. 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="buckleyana" order="Poales" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="buckleyana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">buckleyana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="stenophylla" order="Poales" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="stenophylla">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">stenophylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are intermediate to var. 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="scabrella" order="Poales" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="scabrella">scabrella</taxonomicName>
, but are too smooth to be included in the latter variety. 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.65332" author="Hitchcock, AS" journalOrPublisher="Carnegie Institution of Washington publication" pageId="15" pageNumber="116" refId="B17" refString="Hitchcock, AS, 1951. Manual of the Grasses of the United States (2nd edn, A. Chase). US Department of Agriculture, Washington, D.C. https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.65332" title="Manual of the Grasses of the United States (2 nd edn, A. Chase). US Department of Agriculture, Washington, D. C." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.65332" year="1951">Hitchcock (1951)</bibRefCitation>
equated 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="stenophylla" order="Poales" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="stenophylla">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">stenophylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with var. 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="var. gracillima" order="Poales" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="variety" species="stenophylla" variety="gracillima">gracillima</taxonomicName>
, but we agree with Keck (Suppl. material 2) in equating it with the 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="incurva" order="Poales" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="incurva">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">incurva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
form. 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Poa tenuifolia" order="Poales" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tenuifolia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">Poa tenuifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Nutt. ex S. 
<bibRefCitation author="Watson, S" journalOrPublisher="Nordic Journal of Botany" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" refId="B43" refString="Watson, S, 1871. United States Geological Expolration [sic] of the Fortieth Parallel. Vol. 5, Botany. Government Printing Office, Washington D.C., 1-525." title="United States Geological Expolration [sic] of the Fortieth Parallel. Vol. 5, Botany. Government Printing Office, Washington D. C., 1 - 525." year="1871">Watson (1871)</bibRefCitation>
, nom. illeg., was described from heterogeneous original material (at US, distributed as 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">S. Watson 1318</emphasis>
): E. Humboldt Mts. = var. 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="var. juncifolia" order="Poales" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="tenuifolia" variety="juncifolia">juncifolia</taxonomicName>
; Virginia Mts. = var. 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="secunda" order="Poales" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="secunda">secunda</taxonomicName>
; Diamond Mts. = var. 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="var. scabrella" order="Poales" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="secunda" variety="scabrella">scabrella</taxonomicName>
. However, Watson also cited &quot; 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Poa tenuifolia" order="Poales" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tenuifolia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">Poa tenuifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Nutt., ms. In Herb.&quot; The Nuttall specimen with that name is at PH (PH00020091) and 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. tenuifolia" order="Poales" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="tenuifolia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">P. tenuifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation author="Buckley, SB" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia" pageId="15" pageNumber="116" pagination="88 - 101" refId="B4" refString="Buckley, SB, 1862. Description of plants. No. 3 - Gramineae. Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia 14: 88 - 101" title="Description of plants. No. 3 - Gramineae." volume="14" year="1862">Buckley (1862)</bibRefCitation>
is based on that specimen. Therefore, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Watson’s">Watson's</normalizedToken>
taxon name is superfluous.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="113" type="habitat">
<paragraph pageId="12" pageNumber="113">Habitat and range.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="12" pageNumber="113">
Open forests, steppe, and alpine, generally in light, well-drained soils. Range of the subspecies (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Distribution of Poa secunda subspecies in North America: subsp. secunda (yellow); subsp. juncifolia (blue)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.110.27750.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/240277" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">2B</figureCitation>
), but mostly replaced by var. 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="scabrella" order="Poales" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="scabrella">scabrella</taxonomicName>
on west side of the Sierra Nevada and westwards and in the Mojave Desert.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="113" type="chromosome numbers">
<paragraph pageId="12" pageNumber="113">Chromosome numbers.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="12" pageNumber="113">
Numbers reported as 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. secunda" order="Poales" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="secunda">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">P. secunda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and avowed synonyms: 2 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">n</emphasis>
= 42, 56, ≈ 68, 70 (x2), ≈ 70 (x2), ≈ 74, ≈ 78 (x2), 81, 81, 82 (x2), 84 (x2), 84-88+II, ≈ 84, 85-87, 86 (x2), ≈ 87, ≈ 99, 104. The one count of 2 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">n</emphasis>
= 42 was reported by 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1139/b61-010" author="Bowden, WM" journalOrPublisher="Canadian Journal of Botany" pageId="15" pageNumber="116" pagination="123 - 138" refId="B3" refString="Bowden, WM, 1961. Chromosome numbers and taxonomic notes on northern grasses. IV. Tribe Festuceae: Poa and Puccinellia. Canadian Journal of Botany 39: 123 - 138, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1139/b61-010" title="Chromosome numbers and taxonomic notes on northern grasses. IV. Tribe Festuceae: Poa and Puccinellia." url="https://doi.org/10.1139/b61-010" volume="39" year="1961">Bowden (1961)</bibRefCitation>
originated from Alberta. Numbers originally reported as 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. canbyi" order="Poales" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="canbyi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">P. canbyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: 2 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">n</emphasis>
= 56, 70 (x4), ≈ 72, ≈ 82 (x2), ≈ 83, 84 (x4), ≈ 84 (x2), 85, ≈ 86. Keck (in 
<bibRefCitation author="Munz, PA" journalOrPublisher="University of California Press, Berkeley" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" refId="B27" refString="Munz, PA, 1959. A California Flora. University of California Press, Berkeley" title="A California Flora." year="1959">Munz 1959</bibRefCitation>
) attributed higher numbers to 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. incurva" order="Poales" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="incurva">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">P. incurva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Numbers secondarily reported as 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. incurva" order="Poales" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="incurva">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">P. incurva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: 2 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">n</emphasis>
= 90, 93, 94, 99, 105-106.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
